3:"compatibility";a:1:{s:5:"3.3.1";a:1:{s:3:"1.0";a:3:{i:0;i:100;i:1;i:2;i:2;i:2;}}}s:6:"rating";d:60;s:11:"num_ratings";i:2;s:8:"homepage";s:47:"https://www.grendelman.net/wp/nextgen-enhancer/";s:11:"description";s:996:"<p>This plugin enhances the functionality of NextGEN Gallery. Its features:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Retaining meta-data across image operations, like resizing.</li>\n<li>Automatic management of image descriptions, using various sources of information.</li>\n<li>Video support in galleries. Videos can be played with your favorite flash\nplayer. No HTML5 yet.</li>\n<li>Page pre- and suffixes for gallery pages. Useful with Hidepost, for example.</li>\n<li>Tzzbox overlay effect, because Lightshadowboxviewclone just isn''t good enough.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>It needs NextGEN Gallery version 1.9.0 or higher.</p>\n\n<p>A warning up front: THIS PLUGIN IS NOT FOR EVERYBODY.</p>\n\n<p>It makes certain assumptions about how your content is organised, and it makes\nchanges to your NextGEN Gallery database, although it is configurable in many\nways, and is relatively safe to use.</p>\n\n<p>Please refer to\n<a href="https://github.com/tinuzz/wp-plugin-nextgen-enhancer/blob/master/README.rdoc">github</a>\nfor more information.</p>";s:17:"short_description";s:83:"This plugins enhances the functionality of NextGEN Gallery version 1.9.0 or higher.";}i:21;O:8:"stdClass":14:{s:4:"name";s:39:"WP Smush.it NextGEN Gallery Integration";s:4:"slug";s:38:"wp-smushit-nextgen-gallery-integration";s:7:"version";s:5:"0.1.0";s:6:"author";s:40:"<a href="http://dialect.ca/">Dialect</a>";s:14:"author_profile";s:53:"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/profile/alexdunae";s:12:"contributors";a:1:{s:9:"alexdunae";s:53:"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/profile/alexdunae";}s:8:"requires";s:3:"2.9";s:6:"tested";s:5:"3.2.1";s:13:"compatibility";a:0:{}s:6:"rating";i:0;s:11:"num_ratings";i:0;s:8:"homepage";s:34:"http://dialect.ca/code/wp-smushit/";s:11:"description";s:384:"<p>This is a very basic integration made by popular request: the only thing it does is smushes new images.</p>\n\n<p>We don''t use NextGEN Gallery, so anyone wanting more functionality (re-smush, bulk smush, etc...) is encouraged to dive in and contribute.</p>\n\n<p>Plugin updates are announced on <a href="http://www.twitter.com/TheCHANGELOG">http://www.twitter.com/TheCHANGELOG</a>.</p>";s:17:"short_description";s:98:"Reduce image file sizes and improve performance using the Smush.it API via the WP Smush.it plugin.";}i:22;O:8:"stdClass":14:{s:4:"name";s:23:"YD Network Wide NextGen";s:4:"slug";s:23:"yd-network-wide-nextgen";s:7:"version";s:5:"0.1.0";s:6:"author";s:46:"<a href="http://www.yann.com/">Yann Dubois</a>";s:14:"author_profile";s:51:"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/profile/ydubois";s:12:"contributors";a:1:{s:7:"ydubois";s:51:"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/profile/ydubois";}s:8:"requires";s:5:"3.0.1";s:6:"tested";s:5:"3.0.5";s:13:"compatibility";a:5:{s:5:"3.0.1";a:1:{s:5:"0.1.0";a:3:{i:0;i:100;i:1;i:1;i:2;i:1;}}s:5:"3.0.2";a:1:{s:5:"0.1.0";a:3:{i:0;i:100;i:1;i:1;i:2;i:1;}}s:5:"3.0.3";a:1:{s:5:"0.1.0";a:3:{i:0;i:100;i:1;i:1;i:2;i:1;}}s:5:"3.0.4";a:1:{s:5:"0.1.0";a:3:{i:0;i:100;i:1;i:1;i:2;i:1;}}s:5:"3.0.5";a:1:{s:5:"0.1.0";a:3:{i:0;i:100;i:1;i:1;i:2;i:1;}}}s:6:"rating";d:100;s:11:"num_ratings";i:1;s:8:"homepage";s:64:"http://http://www.yann.com/en/wp-plugins/yd-network-wide-nextgen";s:11:"description";s:454:"<h4>Sitewide / Network-wide Galleries and pictures</h4>\n\n<p>This plugin replicates all NGG galleries and images to your SWT aggregation blog.</p>\n\n<p>It is an add-on to the <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/nextgen-gallery/">NextGEN gallery plugin</a> by <a href="http://profiles.wordpress.org/users/alexrabe/">alexrabe</a>. \nIt will not work and is not useful if you do not have the NextGEN plugin installed.</p>\n\n<p>Compatible with PHP5.</p>";s:17:"short_description";s:64:"Description: Network-wide NGG galleries. Similar to SWT for NGG.";}i:23;O:8:"stdClass":14:{s:4:"name";s:47:"User Access Manager - NextGEN Gallery Extension";s:4:"slug";s:45:"user-access-manager-nextgen-gallery-extension";s:7:"version";s:10:"0.1.4 Beta";s:6:"author";s:56:"<a href="http://www.gm-alex.de/">Alexander Schneider</a>";s:14:"author_profile";s:51:"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/profile/gm_alex";s:12:"contributors";a:1:{s:7:"GM_Alex";s:51:"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/profile/gm_alex";}s:8:"requires";s:3:"3.0";s:6:"tested";s:5:"3.0.5";s:13:"compatibility";a:5:{s:5:"3.0.1";a:2:{s:10:"0.1.3 Beta";a:3:{i:0;i:100;i:1;i:1;i:2;i:1;}s:10:"0.1.4 Beta";a:3:{i:0;i:50;i:1;i:2;i:2;i:1;}}s:3:"3.1";a:1:{s:10:"0.1.4 Beta";a:3:{i:0;i:0;i:1;i:2;i:2;i:0;}}s:5:"3.1.3";a:1:{s:10:"0.1.4 Beta";a:3:{i:0;i:50;i:1;i:2;i:2;i:1;}}s:3:"3.2";a:1:{s:10:"0.1.4 Beta";a:3:{i:0;i:100;i:1;i:1;i:2;i:1;}}s:5:"3.2.1";a:1:{s:10:"0.1.4 Beta";a:3:{i:0;i:67;i:1;i:3;i:2;i:2;}}}s:6:"rating";d:100;s:11:"num_ratings";i:3;s:8:"homepage";s:85:"http://www.gm-alex.de/projects/wordpress/plugins/user-access-manager/nextgen-gallery/";s:11:"description";s:871:"<p>This plugin allows you to use the <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/user-access-manager/">User Access Manager</a>-Plugin to control the access for the <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/nextgen-gallery/">NextGEN Galley</a>-Plugin. You can lock Albums, Galleries and Images.</p>\n\n<p>Note: This plugin works only with the current developer version of the NextGEN Gallery-Plugin which you can get <a href="http://code.google.com/p/nextgen-gallery/source/checkout">here</a>.</p>\n\n<p><em>Feature list</em></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Hide albums (if no access)</li>\n<li>User-defined album content (if no access)</li>\n<li>Hide galleries (if no access)</li>\n<li>User-defined gallery title (if no access)</li>\n<li>User-defined gallery content (if no access)</li>\n<li>Hide images (if no access)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><em>Included languages</em></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>English</li>\n</ul>";s:17:"short_description";s:119:"With this plugin you can use the &#34;User Access Manager&#34; to control the access for the &#34;NextGen Gallery&#34;.";}}}', 'no');
